  "title": "Philomel",
  "sourceFile": "Waste_notes/philomel_N.htm",
  "encoding": "windows-1252",
  "html": "\n<div><center>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><font><img src=\"../images/R.gif\"/> <strong>Philomel</strong></font><hr noshade=\"\"/>\n<p>V. Ovid, <i>Metamorphoses</i>, VI, Philomela. [Eliot's\n        note] Eliot refers to the story of Philomela who was\n        raped by Tereus, the husband of her sister Procne. All\n        three are in the end turned into birds; Procne and\n        Philomel into nightingales, and Tereus into a lapwing. </p>\n<p><font><em>reference topics</em></font></p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Metamorphoses_IVPhil.htm\">Ovid's <em>Metamorphoses</em>,\n                </a><br/>\n<a href=\"Metamorphoses_IVPhil.htm\">book IV, Philomela</a></td>\n<td><a href=\"title_A.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Philomela.htm\">Philomela\n                and the Nightingale</a></td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Waste_A.htm\"><font>back to \"The Waste Land\" </font></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</center></div>\n",
  "text": "Philomel V. Ovid, Metamorphoses , VI, Philomela. [Eliot's note] Eliot refers to the story of Philomela who was raped by Tereus, the husband of her sister Procne. All three are in the end turned into birds; Procne and Philomel into nightingales, and Tereus into a lapwing. reference topics Ovid's Metamorphoses , book IV, Philomela Philomela and the Nightingale back to \"The Waste Land\"",
